        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 4:08PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 407 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Faywood, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Faywood and Cookes Peak.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
